OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: John
OL,4,CGillespie
OL,6,FMr Gillespie said: "I landed in the
OL,7,Ffirst week, not actually on D-Day.
OL,8,FWith PLUTO pipelines and so the Royal
OL,9,FNavy put down a buoy mooring at Port-
OL,10,Fen-Bessin on Gold Beach and we ran
OL,11,Fpetrol lines from small tankers -
OL,12,Fships - into storage tanks that we
OL,13,Fbuilt on the beachhead. Storage tanks
OL,14,Fthat had 1,200 tons of petrol. It was
OL,15,Fthree stories high."
OL,17,FMr Gillespie's team also assisted with
OL,18,Fthe link-up to other pipes built as
OL,19,Fthe fighting force moved forwards into
OL,20,FBelgium, Holland and Germany.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
